    <item>
      <title>Image Resizing and Soundcloud embeds</title>
      <link>https://shutowl.github.io/blog/image-resizing/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 21 Jul 2021 19:36:18 -0700</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://shutowl.github.io/blog/image-resizing/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h5 id=&#34;posted-on-july-21-2021&#34;&gt;Posted on July 21, 2021&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;image-resizing&#34;&gt;Image resizing&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;img 
	src=&#34;https://shutowl.github.io/images/pochigga.png&#34;  
	alt=&#34;pochita&#34;  
	class=&#34;left&#34;  
	width=&#34;1000&#34; 
	height=&#34;100&#34;
	/&gt;



I finally figured out how to resize images through Hugo shortcodes.
I mean, just look at this &lt;em&gt;L O N G&lt;/em&gt; boi. He seems to be trapped in some 
pretty strict margins, but it&amp;rsquo;s fine as it is.
I can also make him a &lt;em&gt;T A L L&lt;/em&gt; boi too.

    &lt;img 
	src=&#34;https://shutowl.github.io/images/pochigga.png&#34;  
	alt=&#34;pochita&#34;  
	class=&#34;left&#34;  
	style=&#34;float: center;&#34;  
	width=&#34;100&#34; 
	height=&#34;300&#34;
	/&gt;



I can also position him properly:
&lt;br&gt;

    &lt;img 
	src=&#34;https://shutowl.github.io/images/pochigga.png&#34;  
	alt=&#34;pochita&#34;  
	class=&#34;left&#34;  
	style=&#34;float: left;&#34;  
	width=&#34;60&#34; 
	height=&#34;60&#34;
	/&gt;




    &lt;img 
	src=&#34;https://shutowl.github.io/images/pochigga.png&#34;  
	alt=&#34;pochita&#34;  
	class=&#34;left&#34;  
	style=&#34;float: right;&#34;  
	width=&#34;60&#34; 
	height=&#34;60&#34;
	/&gt;




    &lt;img 
	src=&#34;https://shutowl.github.io/images/pochigga.png&#34;  
	alt=&#34;pochita&#34;  
	class=&#34;left&#34;  
	style=&#34;margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;&#34;  
	width=&#34;60&#34; 
	height=&#34;60&#34;
	/&gt;



&lt;br&gt;
This is the only image I have so far, but I&amp;rsquo;ll add some more later.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;soundcloud-embeds&#34;&gt;Soundcloud embeds&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I also managed to get soundcloud embeds working through shortcodes as well.
As a dark theme user, I don&amp;rsquo;t really like their white background. There&amp;rsquo;s probably
a way to change it through CSS or HTML, but I haven&amp;rsquo;t found a solution yet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For now, they&amp;rsquo;ll just look like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;script src=&#34;http://w.soundcloud.com/player/api.js&#34; type=&#34;text/javascript&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;iframe
    width=&#34;100%&#34;
    height=&#34;120&#34;
    scrolling=&#34;no&#34;
    frameborder=&#34;no&#34;
    allow=&#34;autoplay&#34;
    src=&#34;https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1086448648&amp;color=%23ff5500&amp;auto_play=false&amp;hide_related=true&amp;show_comments=true&amp;show_user=true&amp;show_reposts=false&amp;show_teaser=true&#34;
&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
	&lt;!-- raw HTML omitted --&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>The beginning of the website</title>
      <link>https://shutowl.github.io/blog/beginning-of-website/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 19 Jul 2021 21:54:05 -0700</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://shutowl.github.io/blog/beginning-of-website/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h5 id=&#34;posted-on-july-19-2021&#34;&gt;Posted on July 19, 2021&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today I felt like making a website. I mean, I had always meant to do it at one point,
but I had always put it off until today. &lt;a href=&#34;https://pages.github.com/&#34;&gt;Github Pages&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/&#34;&gt;Hugo&lt;/a&gt; 
made it seem like it would be pretty easy to make one, but boy was I wrong. I spent pretty much all day trying to get it
to work, but at least it seems to work now, even if it does look pretty barebones right now.
I still gotta learn a bunch of stuff to make this blog look a little better, so I&amp;rsquo;ll work
on this website for now before diving into other things.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://shutowl.github.io/images/pochigga.png&#34; alt=&#34;maidpochita&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I also need to figure out how to format images like this on these sites too lmao&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
